SIMPLE: riser
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Riser
<hw>Ris"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
rises; <as>as, an early <ex>riser</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The upright piece of
a step, from tread to tread.</def> <specif>Hence:</specif> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Any small upright face, as of a seat, platform, veranda, or the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A shaft excavated from below
upward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <def>A feed head. See under
<er>Feed</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rish</ent>⟦br⟧
